# Trivy ignore file for govee2mqtt
# Filters out base image vulnerabilities that don't apply to a Python MQTT application
#
# This application is a Python-based MQTT bridge that:
# - Doesn't use system command-line utilities (tar, perl, util-linux, etc.)
# - Doesn't call curl/libssh/GnuTLS binaries (Python has native libraries)
# - Doesn't use databases (sqlite) or XML parsing (expat)
# - Doesn't use LDAP, Kerberos, or SSH protocols
# - Runs in an ephemeral container with no persistent storage or shell access
#
# NOTE: These CVEs may have any upstream severity rating, but are assessed as
# low/no risk for this specific application context after manual review.

# ============================================================================
# GLIBC - Low-level C library vulnerabilities not exploitable in Python context
# ============================================================================

# memalign integer overflow - requires attacker control of alignment args
# with very specific large values [1<<62+1, 1<<63]. Python doesn't expose
# memalign to user code and app doesn't take input controlling alignment.
CVE-2026-0861

# getnetbyaddr info disclosure - requires calling with zero-valued network
# and specific nsswitch.conf. Python doesn't call getnetbyaddr this way.
CVE-2026-0915

# wordexp WRDE_REUSE/WRDE_APPEND returns uninitialized memory
# Python doesn't expose wordexp to user code
CVE-2025-15281

# Older glibc issues - various DoS/overflow issues not exploitable via Python
CVE-2010-4756
CVE-2018-20796
CVE-2019-1010022
CVE-2019-1010023
CVE-2019-1010024
CVE-2019-1010025
CVE-2019-9192

